Senior executives from China's largest privately-owned automaker Geely are to meet their Daimler counterparts next week, after announcing on Friday an almost 10 percent stake in the German auto giant, according to sources close to the company. Two sources familiar with the deal told the Reuters news agency that Geely also hopes to meet top German government officials in Berlin about the investment in the maker of Mercedes-Benz and a number of other car, bus, truck and motorcycle brands. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
